	       	     </div>
	
</div>                      <p class="introduction" id="story_continues_1">The Electoral Commission says preparations for the Scottish independence referendum are going well but it raised some concerns.</p>
        <p>John McCormick, electoral commissioner for Scotland, said he was &quot;encouraged&quot; by the progress so far.</p>
        <p>But he called for &quot;clarity&quot; about how the terms of independence would be decided in order to help voters.</p>
        <p>The referendum, on 18 September 2014, will ask &quot;Should Scotland be an independent country?&quot;.</p>
        <p>Mr McCormick said voters need to have absolute confidence in the result.</p>
        <p>He said: &quot;There must be no doubt that the referendum was fair and transparent and there were no barriers to voters or campaigners taking part.</p>
  <!--  Embedding the audio player -->
<!--  This is the embedded player component -->


	
 



